![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/18b0e6d3-8cc1-4d67-840b-3cf0de9ecb52/20240528_180452.jpg)

Pro Wrestling fans were surprised to see TNA Knockouts Champion Jordynne Grace appear in NXT, and it appears this might be just the beginning of a collaboration between the two promotions.

According to reports, Grace's appearance at NXT and upcoming appearance at Battleground may not be a one-time thing. There is a belief that there will be more cross-promotional events between WWE's NXT brand and TNA in the future. This could potentially include NXT wrestlers appearing on TNA programming.

The implications of this potential partnership are significant. For years, WWE has been the dominant force in professional wrestling, and TNA has been seen as the alternative. A collaboration between the two promotions could create a more exciting and competitive landscape for wrestling fans.